  "description": "An L9 envelope carrying an SSTP message over the SAB subprotocol.\n\nSAB (Semantic Alignment via Bargaining) is a subprotocol of SSTP that\nenables agents to reach semantic alignment through a bargaining process\nimplemented with NegMAS Stacked Alternating Offers (SAO).\n\nKind / subkind mapping\n----------------------\nSSTP kind            L9 kind       L9 subkind\n\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500    \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500    \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nintent               contingency   negotiate\nnegotiate            contingency   negotiate\ncommit / agreement   commit        converged\ncommit / disagree    commit        disagreement\ncommit / broken|err  commit        timeout",
  "properties": {
    "header": {
      "$ref": "#/$defs/SABHeader"
    },
    "payload": {
      "$ref": "#/$defs/SABL9Payload"
    }
  },
  "required": [
    "header",
    "payload"
  ],
  "title": "SAB_L9",
  "type": "object",
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "version": "0.1.0",
  "subprotocol": "SAB",
  "protocol": "SSTP"
